          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were a small tobacco farmer in rural Virginia at the start of the Revolutionary War. Initially neutral as to the politics of the war, you fought back when the redcoats tried to take your farm and livestock. You fought back, hard enough to impress your sire who appreciated your principled stance. He brought you into the Anarch Movement, of which you were a firm member for most of your unlife, moving to San Francisco and the Free State there in the mid-19th century. But then the Asian vampires came, who destroyed the dream of the Free States and pitted brother against brother. You saw many former comrades cut down, and others join the New Promise Mandarinate under duress, and you rebelled. As much as you've disliked the Camarilla's methods of doing business, they're miles better than the NPM; and you need someone to have your back in this world. You hope to lead and change by example; to demonstrate to the Camarilla that free warriors will always outmatch those drafted or pressed into duty"
        ],
